SolarCity Corporation Key Developments

SolarCity Corp Shutters South Carolina Office After Short Stint
Jul 7 17
SolarCity Corp. has closed its South Carolina office less than a year after expanding into the state. The news comes seven months after Elon Musk's Tesla Motors Inc. acquired the solar installation company and just two months after the electric car manufacturer decided to shut down SolarCity's door-to-door sales. SolarCity opened its operations in October 2016 and had covered a triangular area between Charleston, Columbia and near Hilton Head Island.


SolarCity Corporation Presents at Solar Power Finance & Investment Summit 2017, Mar-21-2017 through Mar-23-2017
Feb 24 17
SolarCity Corporation Presents at Solar Power Finance & Investment Summit 2017, Mar-21-2017 through Mar-23-2017. Venue: San Diego, California, United States. Presentation Date & Speakers: Mar-21-2017, Albert Luu, Vice President, Structured Finance & Strategy. Mar-22-2017, Albert Luu, Vice President, Global Capital Markets.


SolarCity Corporation Enters into Fourteenth Amendment to Certain Amended and Restated Credit Agreement
Jan 6 17
SolarCity Corporation, Bank of America, N.A., as administrative agent, and the lenders from time to time party thereto entered into a fourteenth amendment to that certain amended and restated credit agreement, dated November 1, 2013, among the company, the administrative agent and the lenders, and as previously amended (the credit facility). Amendment no. 14 amends the credit facility to, among other things, allow for the addition of a new lender under the credit facility.


