Answer:

The best way to determine how much solar you need is to have the solar installer get up on you roof to evaluate it prior to providing you with a solar proposal. The size of the solar system is determined by your roof size, pitch and shading issues as well as the annual kilowatt (kW) usage for each individual home. You and your neighbor could have the exact same size home but entirely different electric usage habits and would each require a different sized system to offset your usage. An average size installation in the Bay Area is between...

